<h1>Andy Bell</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="https://andy-bell.co.uk/now">andy-bell.co.uk/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Cheltenham
England
United Kingdom
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Designer for WriteUpp 
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I'm a designer making slick, accessible and responsive websites with HTML5, CSS3 and JavaScript.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I get a real kick out of making UIs that are easy to use and accessible. It’s the core of everything I do and I’ll happily remove ‘bells and whistles’ for user friendliness, without a second thought.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
“A user interface is like a joke. If you have to explain it, it’s not that good."
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
"Trust Me, I'm Lying: Confessions of a Media Manipulator" by Ryan Holiday
</p>

